defaultMr Willettsdefault: The mortgage loan book will be a completely different type of sale, and we have expert advisers working on it.
defaultMichael Harrisondefault: In relation to the mortgage-style sale, that was exactly one of the issues we looked at.  The view was that the proportion of the loan book being repaid was very small; it was only 14%.  Therefore, the value we would get back, even on a profit share-type arrangement, would have been quite low.  The additional value we would get from having an up
default-
defaultfront payment where all the systems and knowledge were transferred to the new buyer would be greater.  That was part of our work.
