default&#x2011;
default14.  When there was a signal of a budget pressure, we acted and, as a result, the growth 
defaultin the number of students at alternative providers will be much less than previously forecast.  We have done that and we have done it in time.  We have also attached a range of conditions to the designation of a course—both quality conditions and agreement to participate in number controls—that were not set in the past.  I would say that we have to get the balance right.  We want diversity but we have to live within our budgets.
